xecutive%20for%20Special%20Operations%20Command%20(SOCOM)%2C%20said%20the%20strength%20in%20the%20process%20is%20that%20decision-making%20on%20what%20systems%20to%20acquire%20and%20when%20is%20made%20through%20close%20coordination%20with%20the%20operator%2C%20creating%20a%20stronger%20relationship%20between%20what%20the%20individual%20operator%20sees%20as%20necessary%20and%20what%20industry%20partners%20can%20provide.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20the%20recipe%C2%A0is%20really%20simple%2C%26quot%3B%20Johnson%20said%20at%20the%20symposium%2C%20adding%20that%20%26quot%3Bit's%20the%20mindset%20and%20culture%20of%20being%20able%20to%20take%20the%20magic%20that%20happens%20at%20SOCOM%2C%20the%20way%20we%20do%20business%2C%20and%20how%20do%20we%20scale%20that%20and%20get%20that%20across%20the%20department.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20slows%20down%20DoD%20acquisition%3F%20There%20are%20a%20range%20of%20different%20factors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20officials%20said%20recently%2C%20many%20of%20the%20problems%20are%20due%20to%20the%20way%20funding%20is%20appropriated%20and%20how%20contracting%20works%20across%20the%20services%20and%20Congress.%20The%20other%20complication%20is%20the%20requirements%20piece%20and%20whether%20some%20are%20too%20complicated%20and%20arbitrary%20for%20certain%20systems.%20Smith%20referenced%20lengthy%20and%20sometimes%20unnecessary%20requirements%20for%20some%20things%2C%20such%20as%20paint%20on%20the%C2%A0littoral%20combat%20ship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20not%20as%20though%20US%20special%20operations%20forces%20are%20not%20without%20their%20own%20acquisition%20problems.%20For%20instance%2C%20special%20operations%20commanders%20told%20the%20House%20Armed%20Services%20Committee%20last%20week%20that%20US%20adversaries%20are%20modernizing%20faster%20than%20they%20can%2C%20telling%20congressional%20leaders%20that%20sometimes%20technology%20is%20already%20obsolete%20by%20the%20time%20it's%20fielded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D