%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Sabina%20Hitchen%2C%20the%2045-year-old%20founder%20of%20Press%20for%20Success.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20worked%20in%20PR%20for%20years%20before%20starting%20my%20company%2C%20Press%20for%20Success%2C%20a%20PR%20platform%20and%20community%2C%20in%202017.%20My%20husband%2C%20Alex%2C%20has%20worked%20in%20media%20since%20he%20was%2018.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20met%20in%202012%20when%20I%20was%20running%20from%20a%20rainstorm%20in%20NYC%20and%20went%20into%20a%20restaurant%20where%20he'd%20walked%20in%20the%20other%20entrance%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20like%20a%20romcom.%20I%20just%20wanted%20to%20read%20with%20a%20glass%20of%20wine%2C%20and%20he%20came%20up%20and%20sat%20with%20me.%20We%20haven't%20stopped%20talking%20since.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20finally%20decided%20to%20go%20'Facebook%20official%2C'%20we%20realized%20we%20had%20200%20friends%20in%20common%20but%20had%20never%20met.%20Even%20with%20his%20background%2C%20I%20never%20expected%20to%20hire%20him%20for%20my%20company.%20Now%2C%20he's%20my%20employee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227f1b887d-c315-4d57-a454-c4e3dc51a31f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELike%20most%20couples%2C%20we%20used%20to%20weigh%20in%20on%20each%20other's%20work%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20there%20when%20I%20had%20the%20idea%20of%20Press%20for%20Success%3B%20he%20even%20named%20it%20when%20we%20were%20newly%20married.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20year%20before%20the%20pandemic%2C%20he%20left%20his%209-5%20job%20in%20media%20to%20start%20media%20consulting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20pandemic%20hit%2C%20our%20daughter%20was%20very%20young%2C%20and%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20quit%20my%20job.%20I%20love%20being%20a%20mother%2C%20but%20I%20saw%20so%20many%20women%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleft-high-paying-job-be-stay-at-home-mom-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eleaving%20their%20jobs%20to%20care%20for%20their%20kids%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20I%20knew%20that%20wasn't%20the%20right%20decision%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cb2f6129-57d3-476b-b869-9764c6fd9c9d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20decided%20my%20husband%20would%20quit%20his%20job%20instead%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20became%20our%20daughter's%20full-time%20caregiver%20so%20I%20could%20build%20my%20business.%20He%20quit%20in%20July%202020%2C%20and%20we%20lost%20about%2060%25%20of%20our%20income%20as%20I%20had%20returned%20to%20my%20business%20after%20working%20at%20less%20than%20full%20steam%20as%20a%20new%20mom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20worked%2024%2F7%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffemale-breadwinner-supports-husband-stays-home-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebecome%20our%20primary%20breadwinner%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20started%20making%20enough%20to%20make%20up%20for%20his%20lost%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20year%20into%20that%20setup%2C%20he%20suggested%20we%20either%20move%20back%20to%20NYC%20and%20he'd%20start%20working%20in%20consulting%20again%20(we'd%20been%20staying%20in%20Maine%20during%20the%20pandemic%20as%20an%20escape%20from%20the%20city)%20or%20we%20figure%20out%20something%20else.%20That's%20when%20I%20considered%20hiring%20him%20as%20VP%20of%20strategic%20partnerships%20and%20collaboration%20for%20my%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222ac0a1b8-59c4-4816-b5b3-be2837d73b51%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHis%20skillset%20fit%20what%20I%20needed%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20want%20to%20hire%20him%20because%20he%20was%20my%20husband%20or%20needed%20work%20%E2%80%94%20his%20skills%20fit%20my%20company's%20needs.%20I%20needed%20someone%20who%20understood%20media%20and%20PR%20and%20could%20inspire%20people%20and%20command%20a%20room.%20We%20decided%2C%20%26quot%3BLet's%20just%20see%20what%20happens.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20joined%20my%20small%20team%20and%20took%20a%20slight%20pay%20cut%2C%20but%20we%20see%20this%20as%20an%20investment%20in%20something%20bigger.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcouples-therapy-surprising-truths-queer-couple-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaw%20a%20therapist%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20ensure%20we%20were%20approaching%20it%20correctly.%20She%20told%20us%20to%20give%20ourselves%20six%20months%20to%20see%20if%20it%20felt%20right%2C%20and%20if%20it%20didn't%2C%20we%20could%20walk%20away%20without%20it%20being%20a%20failure%20in%20our%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20worked.%20There%20are%20days%20when%20one%20of%20us%20has%20been%20hurt%20or%20upset%2C%20but%20we%20don't%20hold%20grudges%20and%20move%20past%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ecc65f0e-9410-4f5c-845e-0e3539c8cbb3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHe's%20always%20been%20encouraging%20of%20my%20career%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20used%20to%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BMy%20husband%20works%20with%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BNo%2C%20your%20husband%20works%20for%20you.%26quot%3B%20I%20thought%20that%20was%20so%20sexy.%20He%20knows%20I've%20been%20building%20my%20business%20for%20years%20and%20respects%20what%20I've%20built.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompartmentalization%20makes%20working%20together%20feel%20seamless.%20We%20can%20butt%20heads%20on%20a%20work%20idea%20and%20then%20leave%20it%20behind%20to%20go%20to%20a%20family%20barbecue%20where%20I%20can%20be%20who%20I%20need%20to%20be%20as%20a%20wife%20and%20mom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20both%20take%20our%20daughter%20to%20school%20every%20morning%20and%20on%20the%20way%20there%2C%20we%20sing%20Kidz%20Bop%20and%20jam%20out%20with%20her.%20The%20minute%20it's%20just%20us%20in%20the%20car%2C%20we're%20talking%20about%20workshops%20we're%20planning%20and%20our%20members'%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222043d4c2-77c2-4fcc-84b3-04c623e5c255%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20also%20physically%20separate%20while%20working%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20tried%20to%20work%20in%20the%20same%20space%20initially%2C%20but%20I%20interrupted%20him%20constantly.%20Working%20apart%20while%20Alex%20is%20at%20an%20office%20during%20the%20day%20allows%20me%20to%20miss%20him.%20Having%20separate%20spaces%20gives%20us%20some%20of%20the%20mystery%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20also%20work%20on%20separate%20things%3A%20He%20works%20on%20partnerships%20and%20collaborations%20while%20I'm%20leading%20the%20community%20and%20planning%20workshops.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20working%20on%20individual%20projects%2C%20I%20had%20to%20let%20go%20of%20a%20lot%20of%20ego.%20I%20thought%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20is%20he%20going%20to%20think%20of%20me%20teaching%3F%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20my%20stage%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20when%20I%20shared%20the%20stage%20with%20him%2C%20he%20lit%20up%2C%20and%20people%20loved%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20been%20amazing%2C%20but%20I%20did%20have%20to%20tell%20him%20he%20can't%20call%20me%20darling%20while%20we're%20on%20a%20live%20broadcast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c3be4719-149a-4e31-8261-02951ec5f3ed%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20also%20prioritize%20having%20date%20nights%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20beginning%2C%20every%20time%20my%20parents%20would%20babysit%2C%20we%20would%20work%20through%20our%20date%20nights.%20I%20forgot%20what%20it%20was%20like%20to%20date%20my%20husband.%20Now%2C%20we%20plan%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboring-dates-ruining-marriage-how-we-fixed-it-fun-adrenaline-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20fun%20date%20night%3C%2Fa%3E%20weekly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoing%20business%20well%20is%20like%20forced%20therapy%20on%20yourself%2C%20which%20is%20the%20same%20as%20marriage.%20Many%20people%20say%20it's%20a%20risk%20working%20together%2C%20but%20it%20gives%20us%20power%20over%20our%20family's%20destiny.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20he%20joined%20the%20company%2C%20it%20has%20grown%20in%20every%20way%2C%20including%20revenue.%20What%20started%20as%20a%20course%20platform%20is%20now%20a%20thriving%20membership%20community%20with%20a%20new%20platform%2C%20an%20app%2C%20and%20soon-to-come%20real-time%20text%20alerts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20get%20to%20do%20what%20I%20love%20with%20the%20person%20I%20love%20for%20a%20higher%20purpose%2C%20which%20feels%20amazing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhired-husband-role-my-company-saw-therapist-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1741082702000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67c609ea69253ccddf982039%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhired-husband-role-my-company-saw-therapist-2025-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22When%20Sabina%20Hitchen's%20husband%20was%20looking%20for%20work%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20she%20hired%20him%20for%20a%20role%20at%20her%20business.%20They%20work%20from%20separate%20locations.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Jamie%20Phillis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhired-husband-role-my-company-saw-therapist-2025-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Stock%20markets%20fall%20after%20US%20tariffs%20spark%20trade%20war%20fears%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1741082583000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F56ab%2Flive%2F7d758130-f8d5-11ef-8a06-7ba4024a445c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fckg1jxdpq0qo%230%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Stock%20markets%20in%20the%20US%2C%20Asia%20and%20the%20UK%20dip%20after%20Trump%20tariffs%20kicked%20in%20and%20spark%20retaliation.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A86%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fckg1jxdpq0qo%22