wards%20Putin%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ETwo%20days%20after%20US%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20berated%20Ukrainian%20leader%20Volodymyr%20Zelensky%20at%20the%20White%20House%20on%20live%20television%2C%20European%20leaders%20met%20in%20London%20to%20present%20a%20united%20front%20to%20support%20him.%20They%20agreed%20on%20a%20plan%20to%20achieve%20peace%20in%20Ukraine%20with%20some%20security%20guarantees%2C%20though%20they%20still%20want%20the%20US%20to%20provide%20military%20backing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20has%20so%20far%20refused%20to%20commit%20to%20any%2C%20a%20major%20reason%20for%20the%20bust-up%20at%20the%20Oval%20Office%20on%20Friday.%20Unlike%20Europeans'%20strong%20show%20of%20support%20for%20Zelensky%2C%20Trump%20is%20still%20very%20angry%20with%20him%20and%20has%20now%20paused%20military%20aid%20to%20Ukraine.%20This%20came%20after%20the%20Ukrainian%20leader%20said%20that%20the%20end%20of%20war%20with%20Russia%20is%20%26quot%3Bvery%2C%20very%20far%20away%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump's%20shock%20and%20awe%20foreign%20policy%20since%20his%20return%20to%20power%20less%20than%20six%20weeks%20ago%20has%20made%20analysts%20scratch%20their%20heads.%20Why%20is%20he%20abandoning%20Ukraine%2C%20embracing%20Russia%2C%20and%20turning%20his%20back%20on%20an%20alliance%20of%20Western%20liberal%20democracies%2C%20which%20has%20worked%20largely%20successfully%20under%20the%20US%20leadership%20since%20the%20Second%20World%20War%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20explains%20his%20seemingly%20imperialist%20pronouncements%20about%20taking%20over%20Greenland%20and%20the%20Panama%20Canal%2C%20an%20aggressive%20push%20for%20a%20deal%20on%20critical%20minerals%20with%20Ukraine%20and%20imposition%20of%20tariffs%20on%20several%20countries%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Elephant%20In%20The%20Room%3A%20China%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20obvious%20explanation%20of%20Trump's%20actions%20and%20pronouncements%20is%20that%20he%20is%20fulfilling%20the%20campaign%20promise%20of%20his%20America%20First%20policy.%20His%20preference%20for%20strongmen%20like%20the%20Russian%20President%2C%20Vladimir%20Putin%2C%20is%20also%20clear.%20That%20Trump%20is%20not%20a%20fan%20of%20the%20European%20Union%20is%20also%20well-known.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20look%20closely%2C%20and%20you%20will%20find%20China%20at%20the%20core%20of%20his%20new%20foreign%20policy.%20Consider%20Trump's%20statements%20and%20shocking%20pronouncements%2C%20and%20link%20them%20with%20some%20of%20the%20less%20publicised%20actions%20he%20has%20taken%20in%20the%20past%20five%20weeks%2C%20and%20you%20will%20find%20a%20clear%20pattern%20emerging.%20Unlike%20European%20leaders%20who%20still%20see%20Russia%20as%20a%20major%20threat%20to%20their%20security%2C%20Trump%20has%20concluded%20that%20the%20main%20threat%20to%20the%20US%20comes%20from%20China%2C%20the%20world's%20second-biggest%20economy%20after%20his%20own.%20He%20doesn't%20name%20Beijing%20in%20this%20context%2C%20but%20his%20actions%20speak%20for%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWestern%20sanctions%20against%20Russia%20over%20the%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20in%202022%20forced%20Putin%20to%20seek%20China's%20help%2C%20which%20led%20to%20a%20surge%20in%20their%20bilateral%20trade%20to%20more%20than%2026%25%20in%20a%20year.%20Although%20bilateral%20trade%20did%20not%20rise%20as%20much%20in%20the%20following%20two%20years%2C%20Moscow%20still%20banks%20on%20Beijing%20as%20the%20West%2C%20then%20led%20by%20Joe%20Biden%2C%20worked%20to%20isolate%20and%20punish%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWeaning%20Putin%20Away%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20is%20keen%20to%20pull%20Vladimir%20Putin%20from%20Chinese%20President%20Xi%20Jinping's%20lap%2C%20%C2%A0just%20as%20Nixon%20had%20delinked%20China%20from%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20in%20the%201970s.%20He%20appears%20to%20believe%20that%20continuing%20a%20cold%20war%20with%20Russia%20in%20the%2021st%20century%20doesn't%20make%20sense%20when%20it%20doesn't%20threaten%20the%20US%20directly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20wants%20to%20rebuild%20US-Russia%20relations%2C%20something%20Putin%20is%20also%20interested%20in.%20There%20are%20already%20talks%20of%20readmitting%20Putin%20to%20the%20G-7%20fold%20once%20a%20peace%20deal%20over%20Ukraine%20is%20concluded%E2%80%94a%20key%20goal%20of%20Trump%20despite%20last%20Friday's%20events%20in%20Washington.%20Of%20course%2C%20the%20Europeans%20still%20feel%20that%20Moscow%20under%20Putin%20threatens%20their%20security.%20They%20warn%20that%20letting%20him%20win%20in%20Ukraine%20will%20only%20embolden%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20is%20China%20The%20'Main'%20Threat%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20US%20administration%20strongly%20believes%2C%20and%20not%20without%20reason%2C%20that%20it%20is%20China%20that%20is%20their%20main%20adversary%2C%20and%20that%20it%20uses%20unfair%20trade%20practices%20to%20exploit%20America%2C%20illicitly%20tries%20to%20obtain%20US%20technology%20to%20advance%20its%20military%20and%20industrial%20programme%2C%20and%20poses%20a%20serious%20threat%20to%20its%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20also%20believes%20that%20China%20has%20exploited%20globalisation%20to%20its%20advantage.%20It%20uses%20state-owned%20corporations%20that%20are%20heavily%20subsidised%20by%20the%20government%20to%20enter%20markets%20of%20other%20countries%2C%20including%20the%20US.%20They%20invest%20even%20in%20America's%20critical%20industries%20while%20blocking%20US%20firms%20from%20doing%20the%20same%20in%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20presidential%20document%20titled%20%E2%80%98America%20First%20Investment%20Policy'%2C%20signed%20by%20Trump%20over%20a%20week%20ago%2C%20warns%20that%20%E2%80%9CPRC-affiliated%20investors%20are%20targeting%20the%20crown%20jewels%20of%20United%20States%20technology%2C%20food%20supplies%2C%20farmland%2C%20minerals%2C%20natural%20resources%2C%20ports%2C%20and%20shipping%20terminals%E2%80%9D.%20The%20document%20promises%20to%20%E2%80%9Cestablish%20new%20rules%E2%80%9D%20to%20stop%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMinerals%2C%20Minerals%20Everywhere%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump's%20main%20concern%2C%20however%2C%20is%20China's%20control%20of%20critical%20minerals%2C%20including%20graphite%2C%20lithium%2C%20cobalt%20and%20copper%2C%20which%20are%20used%20in%20electric%20car%20batteries%2C%20nuclear%20power%2C%20medical%20equipment%2C%20clean%20energy%20products%2C%20and%20weapons.%20China%20controls%20over%2060%25%20of%20these%20minerals%20and%20the%20refinement%20of%20up%20to%2090%25%20of%20them.%20The%20United%20States%20imports%2041%20of%20the%2050%20critical%20minerals%20listed%20by%20the%20US%20Geological%20Survey.%20China%20is%20the%20largest%20producer%20of%2029%20of%20them%20and%20is%20increasingly%20weaponising%20them%20by%20imposing%20export%20controls%20and%20bans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20explains%20Trump's%20efforts%20to%20secure%20the%20supply%20of%20these%20minerals%20from%20Ukraine%20and%20elsewhere.%20Ukraine%20has%20deposits%20of%20more%20than%2020%20of%20those%2050%20critical%20minerals%2C%20including%20large%20deposits%20of%20titanium%2C%20which%20is%20used%20for%20making%20aircraft%20wings%20and%20other%20aviation%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUkraine%20also%20has%20the%20largest%20uranium%20deposits%20in%20Europe.%20So%2C%20no%20wonder%20Trump%20still%20wants%20to%20sign%20a%20deal%20with%20Kyiv%20for%20these%20minerals%2C%20despite%20Friday's%20shouting%20match%20at%20the%20Oval%20Office.%20Zelensky%20said%20on%20Sunday%20that%20Ukraine%20is%20also%20ready%20to%20sign%20that%20deal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EGreenland%20And%20Panama%20Dreams%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20has%20also%20been%20harvesting%20critical%20minerals%20in%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20world%2C%20despite%20large%20reserves%20at%20home.%20It%20has%20been%20active%20in%20Greenland%20since%202013%2C%20when%20the%20island%20repealed%20a%20law%20banning%20the%20mining%20of%20radioactive%20material%20and%20rare%20earth%20elements.%20It%C2%A0has%20huge%20reserves%20of%20rare%20earth%20minerals%2C%20lithium%2C%20graphite%2C%20copper%2C%20nickel%2C%20zinc%2C%20and%20other%20materials%20used%20in%20green%20technologies.%20Trump%20doesn't%20want%20these%20minerals%20to%20be%20exploited%20by%20China%20and%20is%20keen%20to%20acquire%20the%20territory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20is%20also%20a%20factor%20in%20the%20Trump%20administration's%20interest%20in%20taking%20over%20the%20US-built%20Panama%20Canal.%20There%20has%20been%20increased%20Chinese%20shipping%20activity%20there%20in%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20which%20the%20US%20sees%20as%20a%20threat%20to%20its%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Fentanyl%20Flooding%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20set%20of%20tariffs%20announced%20by%20Trump%20was%20against%20Canada%2C%20Mexico%20and%20China.%20But%20they%20were%20not%20an%20attempt%20to%20address%20the%20trade%20deficit%E2%80%94they%20were%20mainly%20driven%20by%20the%20need%20to%20curb%20the%20import%20of%20Fentanyl%2C%20an%20opioid%20drug%2C%20which%2C%20he%20says%2C%20comes%20primarily%20from%20China.%20It%20is%20up%20to%2050%20times%20more%20potent%20than%20heroin%20and%20is%20largely%20responsible%20for%20the%20opioid%20crisis%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20what%20he%20called%20an%20opening%20salvo%2C%20Trump%2C%20within%2010%20days%20of%20returning%20to%20power%2C%20imposed%2025%25%20tariffs%20on%20Canada%20and%20Mexico%2C%20and%2010%25%20on%20all%20Chinese%20imports%20into%20the%20US.%20Tariffs%20on%20Canada%20and%20Mexico%20were%20suspended%20for%20a%20month%2C%20but%20those%20against%20China%20remained.%20Beijing%20reacted%20with%20its%20own%20set%20of%20tariffs%2C%20which%2C%20not%20surprisingly%2C%20included%20restricting%20the%20supply%20of%2025%20critical%20minerals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%20Trump%20has%20doubled%20the%20tariffs%20on%20China%20to%2020%25%2C%20saying%20that%20Chinese-made%20Fentanyl%20is%20still%20coming%20into%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EDeep%20Concerns%20With%20DeepSeek%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina's%20open-source%20AI%20application%2C%20DeepSeek%2C%20released%20a%20month%20ago%2C%20is%20being%20seen%20in%20Washington%20as%20Beijing's%20latest%20move%20to%20attain%20technological%20dominance%20and%20undermine%20safety%20in%20cyberspace.%C2%A0Two%20Republican%20members%20have%20even%20proposed%20a%20bill%20to%20ban%20the%20app.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeepSeek%20is%20cheap%2C%20does%20not%20use%20high-end%20chips%2C%20and%20is%20more%20energy%20efficient.%20However%2C%20the%20US%20Center%20for%20Strategic%20and%20International%20Studies%20warns%20that%20%26quot%3Bwhile%20open-source%20models%20can%20be%20made%20secure%20when%20built%20with%20strong%20safety%20guardrails%2C%20DeepSeek's%20design%20allows%20users%20to%20alter%20not%20only%20its%20functionalities%20but%20also%20its%20safety%20mechanisms%2C%20creating%20a%20far%20greater%20risk%20of%20exploitation%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20US%20agencies%2C%20such%20as%20NASA%20and%20the%20US%20Navy%2C%20have%20asked%20employees%20not%20to%20use%20DeepSeek%20due%20to%20national%20security%20concerns.%20Trump%20has%20signed%20an%20executive%20order%20asking%20his%20officials%20to%20prepare%20an%20action%20plan%20on%20AI%20within%20180%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBeijing%20Is%20Now%20More%20Prepared%20Too%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20in%20his%20first%20term%20had%20announced%20a%20slew%20of%20tariffs%20against%20China%2C%20after%20which%20the%20Biden%20administration%20also%20imposed%20its%20own.%20But%20China%20has%20only%20toughened%20its%20stance%20and%20is%20now%20more%20prepared%20to%20respond%20to%20such%20pressures.%20Even%20before%20Trump%20began%20his%20second%20term%2C%20Beijing%20announced%20an%20embargo%20on%20four%20critical%20minerals%20to%20the%20United%20States.%20It%20also%20ordered%20four%20government-linked%20trade%20associations%20to%20direct%20their%20companies%20to%20avoid%20buying%20American%20computer%20chips.%20Additionally%2C%20it%20announced%20new%20rules%20favouring%20foreign%20companies%20that%20make%20their%20products%20in%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeijing%20has%20also%20been%20putting%20pressure%20on%20major%20US%20companies%20not%20to%20shift%20their%20production%20facilities%20to%20India%2C%20including%20Apple's%20main%20manufacturing%20partner%2C%20Foxconn.%20According%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EFinancial%20Times%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20Chinese%20officials%20have%20made%20it%20difficult%20for%20the%20Taiwanese%20manufacturer%20to%20send%20machinery%20and%20Chinese%20experts%20to%20India%2C%20where%20Apple%20is%20keen%20to%20build%20its%20supply%20chain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMeasures%2C%20More%20Measures%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20his%20first%20day%20in%20office%2C%20one%20of%20the%20documents%20Trump%20signed%20was%20the%20%E2%80%98American%20First%20Trade%20Policy'%2C%20which%20directed%20officials%20to%20review%20US-China%20trade%20relations%2C%20have%20a%20fresh%20look%20at%20previous%20agreements%20to%20find%20out%20whether%20Beijing%20has%20complied%20with%20their%20terms%2C%20and%20study%20new%20measures%20against%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3ENew%20York%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Trump%20has%20also%20replaced%20a%20few%20officials%20in%20the%20Commerce%20Department.%20For%20example%2C%20Matthew%20S.%20Borman%2C%20a%20former%20deputy%20assistant%20secretary%20for%20export%20administration%2C%20has%20been%20removed%2C%20and%20Landon%20Heid%2C%20who%20advocated%20tighter%20restrictions%20on%20sales%20to%20Chinese%20technology%20companies%20while%20at%20the%20State%20Department%2C%20has%20been%20brought%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20President%20has%20also%20announced%20tariffs%20on%20steel%20imports%20aimed%20mainly%20at%20China.%20In%20another%20action%2C%20his%20administration%20proposed%20to%20impose%20levies%20of%20%241.5%20million%20on%20Chinese-made%20ships%20arriving%20at%20American%20ports.%20As%20many%20as%2020%25%20of%20all%20vessels%20arriving%20at%20American%20ports%20are%20made%20in%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump's%20actions%20against%20China%20could%20create%20economic%20pain%20and%20fuel%20inflation.%20However%2C%20he%20believes%20that%20short-term%20pain%20is%20better%20than%20having%20an%20ongoing%20reliance%20on%20China%3B%20this%20also%20fits%20into%20his%20national%20security%20narrative.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAdvantage%20India%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUS%20measures%20may%20encourage%20other%20countries%20as%20well%20to%20review%20their%20policy%20towards%20China%20and%20its%20state-owned%20firms.%20Although%20Europeans%20still%20see%20Russia%20as%20their%20main%20strategic%20threat%2C%20there%20is%20a%20growing%20recognition%20that%20China%20is%20also%20a%20prominent%20adversary.%20But%20as%20the%20global%20stock%20market%20turmoil%20in%20recent%20weeks%20has%20shown%2C%20the%20China-US%20trade%20war%20will%20impact%20the%20international%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20is%20certainly%20watching%20the%20developments%20in%20Washington%20closely.%20A%20thaw%20in%20Russia-US%20relations%20is%20a%20welcome%20sign%20for%20New%20Delhi%2C%20which%20has%20been%20concerned%20about%20Moscow%20becoming%20more%20reliant%20on%20Beijing%20since%20the%20Ukraine%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20will%20try%20to%20improve%20relations%20with%20India%2C%20but%20India%20knows%20well%20that%20it%20is%20not%20a%20reliable%20partner.%20Beijing%20is%2C%20after%20all%2C%20New%20Delhi's%20main%20strategic%20foe%20and%20a%20security%20challenge.%20India%20has%20also%20suffered%20from%20attempts%20by%20it%20to%20disrupt%20supply%20chains%20of%20vital%20ingredients%20of%20pharma%20and%20other%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20Trump's%20meeting%20in%20Washington%20on%20February%2013%20with%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20the%20two%20leaders%20announced%20the%20launch%20of%20the%20Strategic%20Mineral%20Recovery%20initiative%2C%20a%20new%20US-India%20programme%20to%20recover%20and%20process%20critical%20minerals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20one%20of%20the%20top%20five%20producers%20of%20critical%20minerals%2C%20India%20is%20part%20of%20the%20Mineral%20Security%20Partnership%20with%20the%20United%20States%20and%20is%20keen%20to%20exploit%20American%20technical%20expertise%20to%20process%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPutin%20Is%20Happy%2C%20But%20Cautious%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Kremlin%20is%20obviously%20happy%20with%20Trump's%20overtures%20towards%20Moscow%20and%20his%20treatment%20of%20Zelensky.%20Despite%20accusations%20by%20his%20critics%20that%20he%20is%20now%20doing%20Putin's%20bidding%2C%20Trump%20seems%20set%20to%20continue%20with%20his%20new%20foreign%20policy.%20Normalisation%20of%20relations%20with%20Moscow%20will%20also%20help%20US%20firms%20to%20return%20to%20Russia%2C%20offsetting%20some%20of%20the%20losses%20incurred%20from%20the%20trade%20war%20with%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPutin%2C%20however%2C%20is%20too%20smart%20to%20trust%20the%20new%20US%20administration%20blindly.%20He%20is%20in%20no%20hurry%20to%20abandon%20China%2C%20though%20he%20will%20take%20advantage%20of%20Trump's%20overtures.%20Xi%20is%20also%20keen%20to%20maintain%20his%20country's%20strong%20ties%20with%20Moscow.%20Of%20course%2C%20his%20government%20will%20be%20working%20on%20retaliatory%20steps%20against%20measures%20taken%20by%20Washington.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cem%3E(Naresh%20Kaushik%20is%20a%20former%20editor%20at%20the%20Associated%20Press%20and%20BBC%20News%20and%20is%20based%20in%20London)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22pub