%20for%20thrombocytopenia%2C%20a%20blood%20condition%20that%20can%20prevent%20clotting%20and%20lead%20to%20continued%20bleeding.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20following%20days%2C%20the%20Vatican%20reported%20an%20incrementally%20more%20positive%20picture%2C%20but%20there%20was%20another%20major%20issue%20on%20February%2028.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20pope%20suffered%20%26quot%3Ban%20isolated%20crisis%20of%20bronchospasm%26quot%3B%20--%20a%20tightening%20of%20the%20muscles%20that%20line%20the%20airways%20in%20the%20lungs%20--%20which%20caused%20%26quot%3Ban%20episode%20of%20vomiting%20with%20inhalation%26quot%3B%2C%20the%20Holy%20See%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20began%20%26quot%3Bnon-invasive%20mechanical%20ventilation%26quot%3B%20--%20receiving%20oxygen%20through%20a%20mask%2C%20according%20to%20a%20Vatican%20source%20--%20and%20was%20nevertheless%20reported%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bin%20good%20spirits%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Sunday%2C%20the%20pope's%20condition%20%26quot%3Bremained%20stable%26quot%3B%2C%20the%20Holy%20See%20said%20in%20its%20official%20update%20that%20day%2C%20but%20on%20Monday%20Francis%20suffered%20new%20attacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTwo%20episodes%20of%20acute%20respiratory%20failure%26quot%3B%20were%20due%20to%20a%20%26quot%3Bsignificant%20accumulation%20of%20endobronchial%20mucus%20and%20consequent%20bronchospasm%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDoctors%20performed%20two%20bronchoscopies%20--%20chest%20probes%20--%20in%20order%20to%20remove%20%26quot%3Babundant%20secretions%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20pope%20later%20continued%20to%20use%20an%20oxygen%20mask.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAcute%20respiratory%20failure%20occurs%20when%20the%20lungs%20cannot%20pass%20enough%20oxygen%20into%20the%20blood%2C%20or%20when%20carbon%20dioxide%20builds%20up%20in%20the%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20can%20be%20life-threatening.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWork%20continues%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20pope%20has%20been%20staying%20in%20a%20special%20papal%20suite%20on%20the%2010th%20floor%20of%20the%20Gemelli%20hospital%2C%20praying%20and%20performing%20some%20work%2C%20according%20to%20a%20Vatican%20source.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20has%20been%20reading%20and%20signing%20documents%2C%20notably%20appointments%20of%20bishops%20around%20the%20world%2C%20as%20well%20as%20making%20telephone%20calls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrancis%20has%20twice%20received%20Italian%20Cardinal%20Pietro%20Parolin%2C%20the%20Vatican's%20secretary%20of%20state%2C%20and%20Edgar%20Pena%20Parra%2C%20a%20Venezuelan%20archbishop%20who%20is%20Parolin's%20number%20two.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20he%20has%20not%20been%20seen%20in%20public%20since%20being%20hospitalised%2C%20notably%20missing%20his%20Sunday%20Angelus%20prayers%2C%20which%20during%20previous%20hospital%20stays%20he%20delivered%20from%20the%20Gemelli%20balcony.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20the%20Vatican%20has%20published%20his%20written%20texts%20each%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWell-oiled%20communication%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20notable%20shift%20towards%20transparency%20compared%20to%20previous%20papacies%2C%20the%20Vatican%20has%20been%20providing%20twice-daily%20updates%20on%20Francis's%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20morning%20statement%2C%20normally%20one%20line%20shortly%20after%200700%20GMT%20on%20his%20night's%20sleep%20and%20whether%20he%20has%20eaten%20breakfast%2C%20arrives%20to%20accredited%20reporters%20via%20Telegram%20and%20then%20is%20sent%20via%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20more%20detailed%20medical%20bulletin%20arrives%20around%201800%20GMT%2C%20describing%20the%20pope's%20clinical%20progress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDoctors%20said%20Francis%20himself%20had%20requested%20they%20be%20frank%20about%20his%20medical%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELongest%20hospital%20stay%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20Francis's%20fourth%20hospital%20stay%20since%20he%20became%20pope%20on%